## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All CRITICAL runtime-safety rules are strictly followed in both frontend and backend code paths (null/undefined guards, array checks, proper initial state).
- [ ] Cronjobs dashboard can filter, search, paginate, and perform bulk actions with no runtime errors (including for empty datasets).
- [ ] Editor validates all fields in real time; invalid cron expressions or missing required vars are prevented from saving.
- [ ] Schedule Builder + Timezone handling produce correct nextRunAt values and preview windows.
- [ ] Run Details page displays inputs, traces, logs, diffs, artifacts, and timing with accurate, reversible actions.
- [ ] API layer provides complete CRUD for cronjobs, run initiation, pause/resume, clone, and revert; all responses validated and sanitized.
- [ ] Security: proper auth checks on all routes; sensitive fields masked in lists; approvals flow enforced when configured.
- [ ] End-to-end tests cover core flows: create cronjob, trigger run, inspect run details, perform revert, and approve if required.
- [ ] Performance: responsive UI with debounced search; pagination scales to large cronjob sets; efficient rendering of run traces and logs.

